<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="209" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1396,1562]" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">
Diagnosis:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Al-Shehbaz" authorityYear="2022" box="[263,428,1396,1417]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Noccaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="klimesii">
<emphasis box="[263,428,1396,1417]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Noccaea klimesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the other congeners in 
<collectingCountry box="[777,829,1396,1418]" name="India" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[839,923,1396,1418]" name="Pakistan" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, and neighboring countries by a combination of linear, falcate fruit 8–12 × 
<quantity box="[385,483,1432,1454]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2 mm</quantity>
with undulate margin, short style exserted beyond the apical fruit notch, and dense, short, compact fruiting raceme.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
