<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="211" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1861,2065]" lastBlockId="2.[136,1452,159,399]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="211" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,319,2005,2029]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">Discussion:</emphasis>
—As recognized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Al-Shehbaz, I. A." box="[542,749,2005,2029]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" refId="ref1434" refString="Al-Shehbaz, I. A. (2015) Brassicaceae. In: Hong, D. Y. (ed.) Flora of Pan-Himalaya, vol. 30. Science Press and Cambridge University Press, 594 pp." type="book" year="2015">Al-Shehbaz (2015)</bibRefCitation>
, there are six perennial 
<taxonomicName box="[1011,1190,2005,2029]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis box="[1011,1104,2006,2029]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">Noccaea</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in Jammu-Kashmir and other parts of 
<collectingCountry box="[284,341,2041,2065]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[352,445,2041,2065]" name="Pakistan" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, and neighboring 
<collectingRegion box="[635,690,2041,2065]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">Tibet</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[704,774,2041,2065]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">China</collectingCountry>
). From all of these, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Al-Shehbaz" authorityYear="2022" box="[984,1098,2041,2065]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Noccaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="klimesii">
<emphasis box="[984,1098,2041,2065]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">N. klimesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished by having linear, falcate fruits undulate at margin and densely compact racemes not or hardly elongated in fruit. It resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hooker &amp; Thomson 1861: 177) Al-Shehbaz (2002: 91)" authorityName="Al-Shehbaz" authorityPageNumber="91" authorityYear="2002" baseAuthorityName="Hooker &amp; Thomson" baseAuthorityPageNumber="177" baseAuthorityYear="1861" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Noccaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="2" pageNumber="211" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cochlearioides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="211">N. cochlearioides</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hooker, J. D. &amp; Thomson, T." box="[311,658,195,219]" pageId="2" pageNumber="211" pagination="128 - 181" refId="ref1724" refString="Hooker, J. D. &amp; Thomson, T. (1861) Praecursores ad Floram Indicam. Journal of the Proceeding of the Linnaean Society, Botany 5: 128 - 181. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8312.1861. tb 01344. x" type="journal article" year="1861">Hooker &amp; Thomson 1861: 177</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Al-Shehbaz, I. A." box="[675,927,195,219]" pageId="2" pageNumber="211" pagination="89 - 91" refId="ref1347" refString="Al-Shehbaz, I. A. (2002) Noccaea nepalensis, a new species from Nepal, and four new combinations in Noccaea (Brassicaceae). Adansonia 24: 89 - 91." type="journal article" year="2002">Al-Shehbaz (2002: 91)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the curved or contorted fruit with undulate margin, but differs by having linear (vs. oblong) fruit 1.5–2 (vs. 3–4) mm wide, 8–10 (vs. 3–5) seeds/ovules per fruit, and styles exserted from (vs. equal to) apical notch of fruit. It also resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyer (2006: 178)" authorityName="Meyer" authorityPageNumber="178" authorityYear="2006" box="[936,1285,267,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Noccaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="2" pageNumber="211" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="swatensis">
<emphasis box="[936,1070,268,291]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="211">N. swatensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Meyer, F. K." box="[1079,1285,267,292]" pageId="2" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 341" refId="ref1904" refString="Meyer, F. K. (2006) Kritische Revision der &quot; Thlaspi &quot; - Arten Europas, Afrikas un Vorderasiens. Spezieller Teil. IX. Noccaea Moench. Haussknechtia Beiheft 12: 1 - 341." type="journal article" year="2006">Meyer (2006: 178)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a species with about the same ovules/seeds and the linear fruits similar in length and width, but these are straight and without undulate margin. The novelty further differs by having short, decumbent stems 2–3 (vs. erect and 5–10) cm tall, fruiting racemes 1–1.5 (vs. to 7) cm long, and somewhat shorter styles 0.23–0.4 (vs. 0.5–1) mm long.
</paragraph>
